            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1964-08-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1964-08-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="102"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d102">
                <head>102. Memorandum for the Record<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d102fn1"
                        >Source: Central Intelligence Agency, DCI Files: Job 80–B01285A, Meetings
                        with LBJ, 1964. No classification marking. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_MCJA1">McCone</persName> on August 5.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1964-08-04">August 4, 1964</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Meeting, 4 August 1964, 12:30
                        p.m.</item>
                    <item>In attendance: The President, <persName corresp="#p_MNRS1"
                            >McNamara</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_VC1">Vance</persName>,
                            <persName corresp="#p_RD1">Rusk</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BGW1"
                            >Ball</persName>, Robert F. Kennedy, <persName corresp="#p_DRS1"
                            >Dillon</persName>, McGeorge Bundy, <persName corresp="#p_RC2">Carl
                            Rowan</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_MCJA1">McCone</persName>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>[Here follows discussion of Vietnam.]</p>
                <p>2. <hi rend="italic">
                        <persName corresp="#p_BGW1">Ball</persName> on Cyprus:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MIII1">Makarios</persName> endeavoring to sabotage the
                    Geneva meeting. Some pluses to this—not all negative. Greek negotiator returns
                    to Geneva today and Papandreou plan for Enosis. Quiet deal with Turks. Leak
                    would destroy effort—Turkish have leased from Greek Govt.</p>
                <p>Time on our side.</p>
                <p>Bundy—relations with Commies and Nasser.<note n="2" xml:id="d102fn2">
                        <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Record of Action No. 2496, August 4, on
                        this meeting reads: “Cyprus: Noted a briefing by Under Secretary of State
                            <persName corresp="#p_BGW1">Ball</persName> on the situation in Cyprus
                        and the status of the current negotiations in Geneva.” (Department of State,
                            <gloss target="#t_SS1">S/S</gloss>-<gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>
                        Files: Lot 70 D 265) In a memorandum to <persName corresp="#p_BGW1"
                            >Ball</persName>, August 4, <persName corresp="#p_KRW1">Komer</persName>
                        expressed surprise at the optimism that <persName corresp="#p_BGW1"
                            >Ball</persName> had shown during the briefing. In an August 4
                        memorandum to the President, <persName corresp="#p_KRW1">Komer</persName>
                        noted that it was time to rethink the Cyprus problem since <persName
                            corresp="#p_MIII1">Makarios</persName> would leak any deal that
                            <persName corresp="#p_AD1">Acheson</persName> worked out. (Both in the
                            <persName>Johnson</persName> Library, National Security File, Country
                        File, Cyprus, Vol. 11, Memos)</note>
                </p>
            </div>
